Headlines.Author: Sam Mamudi
Headlines.Headline: US Financial Stocks Rise, Helped By AIG

PARAGRAPH.#text: By Sam Mamudi Shares of American International Group Inc. AIG recently rose more than 10%, helping the leading financial stocks to lead the market as the sector rose. AIG stock was boosted by news that the insurer has secured three credit facilities totaling $4.3 billion that will provide funding for the company, freeing it from the New York Federal Reserve. The credit facilities are made up of a 364-day and a three-year facility, from which banks will make loans to AIG, and a $1.3 billion letter of credit facility for AIG property and casualty insurance subsidiary Chartis; 36 banks participated in the facilities, said AIG.

#text: NEW YORK (Dow Jones)--Expect more bad news as home builders work through a housing slump not expected to end this year. Sales are down and cancellations are up. Builders are also incurring hefty charges to free themselves from land deals inked during the height of the housing frenzy. Earlier this month, industry leader D.R. Horton
previewed what it will report Thursday: $2 billion in net orders, down almost half from $3.8 billion a year earlier.

Headlines.Author: Dow Jones
Headlines.Headline: Adviser Likes Cash Flow In Software Sector

PARAGRAPH.#text: By Dow Jones BOSTON (Dow Jones) -- Manny Weintraub, head of Integre Advisors in New York, says that while investors should look for stocks that can deliver a target return to their liking, they should also focus on how much money they can lose if something goes wrong. In a radio interview, Weintraub noted that "if you can make a 10% return with things going OK -- with the mid case, and not the best case for positive returns -- then you have a decent investment, or one where you won't lose a lot if you are wrong." Weintraub currently likes the looks of the software sector, where cash flows help to limit the potential for a downturn.

Headlines.BodyHeadline: Adviser Likes Cash Flow In Software Sector

    sedan, a refrigerator, and a house, and gotten married. He and his wife are expecting

branching out into new fields, or seeking acquisitions abroad.
